"reviewcomment":"Driving to work yesterday, I whipped my head around to check my blindspot and hurt my neck. This taught me two important things: 1) I am old, and 2) I need a new pillow. <br><br>I have a squashy synthetic down pillow, which is fine when you&#39;re in college, going to head banging concerts (that&#39;s what the kids call them, I&#39;m sure), but once you hit 30, things start to go rapidly downhill. Things like your neck. And your metabolism. <br><br>Anyway, I went to Keetsa, where Michael greeted me and let me sample every pillow on the floor (the mattresses were really nice, too). The store itself was very peaceful and quiet, tucked away off of King Street. Michael answered all my questions and didn&#39;t pressure me into buying anything. It didn&#39;t feel like a typical mattress store. <br><br>I got two pillows -- one to fix my deteriorating neck/head situation, and one to replace the stinky Tempurpedic pillow that my fiancee loves. I had him try the Keetsa pillow, and the Tempurpedic one went quickly into storage. Huge success! <br><br>I was also pleasantly surprised by the prices. Less expensive than Tempurpedic, and without that gross chemical smell. There is no off-gassing at all with my Keetsa pillows -- they are ready to be used right out of the box, no &#34;airing out&#34; needed.",
