"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"If you think that the Daiso craze was just happening in SoCal, you&#39;re dead wrong. Even in San Franciso, people flock to the handful of locations that are available. WHY? Cause, everything inside the store is a $1.50 or otherwise stated. This along with a few conditions are plastered all throughout the store, even in different languages. Here&#39;s one in Spanish (<a href='http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/daiso-japan-san-francisco-3?select=E7sDIIAaNQevsuioL1qftw#E7sDIIAaNQevsuioL1qftw'>yelp.com/biz_photos/dais…</a>).<br><br>Located, at the Japan Center (East Mall) of Japantown, the green colored sign outside pretty much gives it away (<a href='http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/daiso-japan-san-francisco-3?select=1l029DR0Y-TE0sDix78puw#1l029DR0Y-TE0sDix78puw'>yelp.com/biz_photos/dais…</a>). It&#39;s a decent sized venue, with enough room to move around comfortably. One thing I like about Daiso locations are the consistencies in the products they sell. The main issue is the quick turnover of merchandise, so employees constantly have to stock the store for their popular items.<br><br>THE RULES OF DAISO<br>- Everything inside the store is $1.50, unless otherwise marked.<br>- They don&#39;t accept $100 dollar bills.<br>- Credit Card minimum is $10. Debit Card has no minimum.<br>- VISA &amp; MasterCard are accepted only. Purchases over $20 with a credit card requires a valid ID.<br>- All sales are final. No returns or exchanges.<br>- They only sell BRAND Goods, not Closeout or Factory Second Merchandise.<br><br>The one thing that&#39;s different about this location is the security, which results in a few additional rules. This is the first Daiso location that I&#39;ve seen, which has a guard present. I assume that there&#39;s a lot of 5 finger discounts happening. Shown clearly outside the store is a sign stating the following.<br><br>- Monitored by security camera.<br>- Shoplifters will be prosecuted.<br>- No public restroom.<br><br>Talk about harsh. But, I don&#39;t make the rules and they&#39;re supposedly made to protect you and me. Either way, Daiso will continue to take my hard earned money, on shit I don&#39;t need or sometimes want, regardless of the location. I hate to love you Daiso.",
