"reviewcomment":"I somehow ended up in this area on a Sunday morning - specifically 8AM.  If you have never been to this area at 8AM on a Sunday, well, I am telling you now, don&#39;t.  There is not much open at this hour and the streets are a barren wasteland of homeless and/or cracked out people wandering around.<br><br>Since the place I wanted to go to had not opened yet, this lovely City Target happened to be open at like 8AM - what luck!  I felt like I was lining up for opening night, and I had a few other people join me as well.  The Target folks opened their doors promptly and I was able to go in to escape the weirdness outside.<br><br>This Target is brightly lit and clean.  The signs are all updated and there&#39;s a decent variety of stuff here.  Yes there are those weird touristy shirts and items in the front but I think this is a trademark of all City Targets - the one in Seattle has the same weird assortment of touristy items.<br><br>I had no problems checking out and I even got a bag refund fee for not using a paper bag (I seriously hate this concept of charging for paper bags because I do a lot of shopping and I can&#39;t fit 10 reusable shopping bags in my purse).",
