"reviewcomment":"Don&#39;t go to the LV Flagship store-come HERE at Neiman Marcus!!!<br><br>1)  E-X-C-E-L-L-E-N-T customer service<br>2)  They have a good inventory; don&#39;t let the size of the boutique in NM deceive you; they can only display a certain amount and most is in the back (FYI-do your research BEFORE coming in, i.e. go online)<br><br>Came here on a Wednesday afternoon in January (after eating lunch at The Rotunda upstairs-yum!).  My husband was with me and I wanted to finally test drive small potential belated birthday/Christmas gifts. Artsy, Empriente, Delightful.  <br><br>I got the DELIGHTFUL PM handbag for $1060 and the MINI POUCHETTE Monogram for $295.  LOVE!!!!!!!!!!  The sales associate, Benjamin, was so helpful, sweet and kind.  He pulled out 8 handbags for me and was patient.  There were 2 SA&#39;s when I went in and the other was helping another customer.  There was some foot traffic but they were overall courteous and just nice people.  Good job NM and LV!<br><br>The LV store at Valley Fair was great to me too after test driving many many handbags after 3 visits down there.  My purchase at NM was not planned and felt a little guilty buying here than back near my home in SJ.    <br><br>FYI:  If you&#39;re coming in to browse at luxury stores, just dress a little decent and don&#39;t look like a shmuck.  It&#39;s not Starbuck&#39;s or the local public library.  I wore leggings, nice boots, and a long vince top. Nothing fancy and they totally treated me with respect.",
